      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. but isn't it true that many legal experts and even some judges argue that the 2nd amendment isn't absolute? like, for example, the court has said \"well-regulated\" means there can be some limits. i'm just trying to understand why you're saying they're \"likely\" to be struck down as if it's a settled fact, when it seems like a huge debate in the courts right now.",
